author: sfgate.com
title: Horoscope for Thursday, 10/8/15 by Christopher Renstrom
text:
ARIES. (March 20 - April 19): You resent walking on eggshells, but make the extra effort today. Tensions say more about others' insecurities than yours.
TAURUS. (April 20 - May 20): You find just the thing you've been looking for thanks to the Moon/Venus conjunction. Maybe it's a one-of-a-kind item or the final piece needed to complete a treasured collection.
GEMINI. (May 21 - June 20): Did you give someone the impression you said yes when you meant no? Clear it up now before you wind up in hot water later.
CANCER. (June 21 - July 21): There's a lot of disinformation being floated around this week. It will take careful sleuthing to distinguish fact from fallacy.
LEO. (July 22 - Aug. 22): There has been so much back-and-forth lately that you may have a hard time remembering what you finally agreed to. Ask.
VIRGO. (Aug. 23 - Sept. 22): You wrote off an acquaintance as a snake in the grass, so imagine your shock when she pulls your fat out of the fire. You'd best apologize - and fast!
LIBRA. (Sept. 23 - Oct. 22): You're surprised to see the human side of someone who's always "on." Is it enough to revise your opinion? Perhaps.
SCORPIO. (Oct. 23 - Nov. 21): You suspected something was up, but today's revelation is still a surprise. You'll need some time to ponder the repercussions.
SAGITTARIUS. (Nov. 22 - Dec. 20): You tried being friends with someone but it's not clicking. Do a slow fade and maybe she won't notice.
CAPRICORN. (Dec. 21 - Jan. 19): There's more to a romantic interest than meets the eye. Expect things to get deep. You'll appreciate the added dimension to your life.
AQUARIUS. (Jan. 20 - Feb. 17): The Moon/Venus conjunction shows you choosing between two equally important relationships. Think personally rather than politically.
PISCES. (Feb. 18 - March 19): Even you're mystified as to why you're obsessed with tracking down an obscure piece of trivia. Sometimes it can't be helped. Besides what's wrong with learning something new?
